## What Problem This Solves

Fixes an issue where users who enable a reply usage footer with `/usage full` or `/usage tokens` would lose that footer after an automatic daily or idle session rollover.

This made `/usage` behave differently from other session-level reply preferences such as `/model` and `/thinking`, which already survive rollover.

## Why This Change Was Made

The fix treats `responseUsage` as the same kind of session preference as the existing rollover-preserved behavior fields. It is copied into the new session during stale rollover and fast reset bootstrap, without adding a new stored marker field or a new `--persist` command flag.

This intentionally keeps the product surface small: `/usage full|tokens` persists across rollover by default, and `/usage off` clears the preference.

## User Impact

Users can turn on usage footers once and keep seeing them across daily or idle session rollover. Existing `/usage` commands stay simple:

```text
/usage off|tokens|full|cost
```

No session-store migration is required because no new persisted state shape is introduced.

## Evidence

Real behavior proof from current head `c5238d3eb8`: a production `initSessionState` call was run against a temporary `sessions.json` containing a stale session with `responseUsage: "full"`. The call used an ordinary message, not `/reset`, so this exercises automatic stale daily rollover.

```bash
node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOF'
import fs from "node:fs/promises";
import os from "node:os";
import path from "node:path";
import { initSessionState } from "./src/auto-reply/reply/session.ts";

const root = await fs.mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), "openclaw-usage-rollover-proof-"));
const storePath = path.join(root, "sessions.json");
const sessionKey = "agent:main:proof:usage-rollover";
const existingSessionId = "session-before-daily-reset-usage-proof";
const staleStartedAt = Date.now() - 48 * 60 * 60 * 1000;

await fs.writeFile(storePath, JSON.stringify({
  [sessionKey]: {
    sessionId: existingSessionId,
    updatedAt: staleStartedAt,
    sessionStartedAt: staleStartedAt,
    lastInteractionAt: staleStartedAt,
    responseUsage: "full",
  },
}, null, 2));

const before = JSON.parse(await fs.readFile(storePath, "utf8"))[sessionKey];
const result = await initSessionState({
  ctx: { RawBody: "hello again", ChatType: "channel", SessionKey: sessionKey },
  cfg: { session: { store: storePath } },
  commandAuthorized: true,
});
const after = JSON.parse(await fs.readFile(storePath, "utf8"))[sessionKey];

console.log(JSON.stringify({
  before: { sessionId: before.sessionId, responseUsage: before.responseUsage },
  result: {
    isNewSession: result.isNewSession,
    resetTriggered: result.resetTriggered,
    oldSessionIdReused: result.sessionId === existingSessionId,
    responseUsage: result.sessionEntry.responseUsage,
  },
  after: {
    sessionId: after.sessionId,
    responseUsage: after.responseUsage,
    oldSessionIdReused: after.sessionId === existingSessionId,
  },
}, null, 2));
EOF
```

Observed result:

```json
{
  "before": {
    "sessionId": "session-before-daily-reset-usage-proof",
    "responseUsage": "full"
  },
  "result": {
    "isNewSession": true,
    "resetTriggered": false,
    "oldSessionIdReused": false,
    "responseUsage": "full"
  },
  "after": {
    "sessionId": "15da7265-1884-454d-9d52-3d0a6d0136dd",
    "responseUsage": "full",
    "oldSessionIdReused": false
  }
}
```

